      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "TIMBIMBOO NZ (7) had a tough back row draw and did some work so wasn't disgraced when midfield last time out. Came from this row to score back-to-back wins at this venue prior. Draws wider but with even luck can return to the the winners' lit. DO IT (4) recorded yet another strong performance last start when he came from the back row for third at Shepparton. That made it three placings on the trot so the hoof is on the till. MONTANA PRIDE (5) was good when beaten only 1.7m into third from the back line at this circuit and distance last week. Led from this barrier when winning last month at Kilmore so is looming as a real threat. GALAXY LASS (2) draws better than in the last two outings and was going well prior. Has the speed to be prominent from this barrier. Contender.",
